---
const stats = [
  { count: 20, plus: true, label: 'Years in print' },
  { count: 22, plus: false, label: 'Issues published' },
  { count: 100, plus: true, label: 'Industry partners' },
  { count: 5, plus: false, label: 'Season events' },
];
---
<section class="section ink-chapter" id="about" data-ground="ink">
  <div class="section__inner">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <h2 class="display">Bridging Innovation, <em>Inspiring Excellence</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="issue__grid">
      <div class="issue__copy">
        <p class="lede reveal">Exposition is a student-run industry-engagement platform organised by the Industrial Management Science Students' Association at the Department of Industrial Management, University of Kelaniya. Every year, undergraduates — not a publishing house, not an agency — plan it, report it, and bring in the industry leaders featured in it.</p>
        <hr class="hairline issue__rule reveal" />
        <p class="reveal">At its centre is Exposition Magazine, running for over 20 years and 20+ issues. Around it sits a calendar of live events — a podcast, an industry forum, a career fair, and a national recognition programme — that connect students directly with the people shaping Sri Lankan business and technology.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stats stagger">
        {stats.map((s) => (
          <div class="stat reveal">
            <span class="stat__num">
              <span class="foil-num" data-count={s.count}>0</span>{s.plus && <span class="stat__plus">+</span>}
            </span>
            <span class="stat__label label">{s.label}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
